# 🎯 STEP 4 — Define Interpretation Layer (V1 logic)

We keep this simple and transparent.

```python id="interp"
def interpret_features(f):
    notes = []

    if f.get("pe_ratio") is not None:
        if f["pe_ratio"] < 15:
            notes.append("Valuation: Low P/E (requires context).")
        elif f["pe_ratio"] > 30:
            notes.append("Valuation: High P/E (growth expectations embedded).")

    if f.get("profit_margin") is not None:
        if f["profit_margin"] > 0.2:
            notes.append("Profitability: Strong margins.")
        else:
            notes.append("Profitability: Weak or moderate margins.")

    if f.get("debt_to_equity") is not None:
        if f["debt_to_equity"] > 100:
            notes.append("Risk: High leverage.")
        else:
            notes.append("Risk: Manageable leverage.")

    return notes
```

